Type at the shell:
    ./configure
    make
    sudo make install
The last command will ask for your password.

Non-technical users can ignore the rest.

Variables/options (for configure):
    --prefix
    --exec_prefix
    --bindir
    --datarootdir
    --docdir
    --infodir
    --htmldir
    --mandir
    --man1dir
    --man3dir
    --man5dir
    --man1ext
    --man3ext
    --man5ext
    --libdir
    --srcdir
    --DESTDIR
    --moduledir         Where to install Python modules
    --nogui
    --noguidoc
    --nocli
    --notechdoc         passwdmanfiles, passwdmanapi
    --halt              do nothing.
    --update            See 'configure.2'.
    --help              list things that are not used.
    --verbose